This paper is about improving low-resource Neural Machine Translation (NMT) with multilingual corpora, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes an algorithm for optimizing data selection, which involves machine learning techniques such as sampling and conditioning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions using BLEU scores to evaluate the performance of the algorithm, which is a common metric in NLP and machine translation research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as well. Finally, the paper uses a sampling distribution to select data, which involves probabilistic modeling and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
